"Poured into a standard pint glass, this is certainly a dark beer, but it also has a good finger's width of offwhite foam atop it, dense and lasting. The nose features some good dark-malt aroma, like a European dunkel, toast-crusty not caramel nor roast. I can't find any hops in the smell, though, which is odd for anything labeled ""IPA"". The hops do come through in the flavor, but it's primarily bitterness, without hop flavor. It does have a nice complex malt, all bready, but I think the description IPA is definitely off. This is just a bitter dark ale. As far as ""black IPAs"" go, this isn't a particularly interesting one of the bunch."
