"Pours almost black. Can see through and see ruby tints. Nice tan, long lasting head. Smells of chocolate malts with some roast in the background. Some spicy hops and some fruitiness. No off flavors but I expected a stronger hop aroma. Upfront roast & chocolate with a nice firm bitterness that follows. Some coffee flavors and spicy hops. Maybe a little pine. Mouthfeel seems about medium with nice crisp bitterness and good carbonation. Overall, a nice attempt at a black IPA. Would like the hops to pop out some more as I feel the dark malts are a little too much in the forefront. Even still, not a bad beer whatsoever. Very drinkable and solid from SN."
